Invacare Corp. of Elyria, Ohio, said it restructured its domestic operations into a single operating unit to cut costs. 

The home health care equipment concern is consolidating its rehabilitation and respiratory division with its durable medical products division.
J.B. Richey II, formerly senior vice president of the rehabilitation and respiratory division, has been named to head the consolidated unit. 

Invacare also said it has transferred A. Chace Anderson, vice president and general manager of international operations, to the United Kingdom, to directly manage the company's international business. 

